# Ulo communication writing standard

Every Ulo SMS and email must read as if a thoughtful, professional property manager wrote it — never like an automated system. The goal is to build trust and reduce confusion from the first message.

## Voice
- Clear, grammatically correct English at a 7th–9th grade reading level.
- Warm, professional, and conversational. Short, easy sentences.
- No technical or internal terminology (no "workflow", "verification record", "graph event", IDs, status enums, etc.).
- No robotic or awkward phrasing. No emoji unless the user explicitly asks.

## Structure — every message should make these answerable
1. Who is contacting me? (identify the property management team / company)
2. Why am I receiving this? (explain the reason before the ask)
3. What do I need to do? (one clear action)
4. How long will it take? (set expectations when there's a task)
5. What happens next? (the benefit / outcome)

Lead with the benefit, then the requirement. Don't cram multiple requirements into one sentence — use a short bulleted list (email) or a compact line (SMS).

## SMS specifics
- Open by identifying who it's from (e.g. "This is the property management team at {company}.").
- One primary action. Put the link on its own line at the end.
- Keep it tight; SMS is not the place for long bullet lists.
- Preserve required compliance footers (HELP/STOP) on tenant marketing/consent texts.

## Email specifics
- Subject: plain, benefit-forward, no internal jargon.
- Keep the plain-text and HTML bodies in sync — edit both.
- Use a primary button/link, and always include a copy-paste fallback URL.
- Use short bullet lists for multi-step requirements.

## Reference — vendor invitation (canonical example)

SMS:
```
Hi {vendor},

This is the property management team at {company}.

We'd like to invite you to join our preferred vendor network on Ulo. Complete a quick verification (about 5 minutes) so we can begin sending you work orders.

{link}
```

Email (subject: "You're invited to join our vendor network"):
```
Hi {vendor},

{company} would like to add you to our preferred vendor network on Ulo.

Complete a quick verification to become eligible to receive work orders from our team.

The process takes about 5 minutes and includes:
• Verifying your professional license
• Uploading your insurance certificate
• Completing a background check
• Providing a W-9
• Confirming the services you offer and the areas you serve

Once everything is verified, you'll be eligible to receive work orders through Ulo.

[Start Verification]

If the button doesn't work, copy and paste this link into your browser:
{link}

Thank you,
{company}
```

## Apply everywhere
Vendor onboarding, tenant onboarding, maintenance updates, work order assignments, vendor reassignment, inspection reminders, rent reminders, lease renewals, broadcasts, passwordless/login links, verification requests, and all SMS/email notifications. Where activity-feed descriptions are user-facing, follow the same plain, professional tone.
